```

Or use the helper script:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{{ .Release.Repo }}/main/scripts/install-skills.sh | sh
```

That installs `{{ .Skills.Install }}` by default. This skill should be the primary entrypoint: it checks whether `{{ .Manifest.Name }}` is already on `PATH`, installs it if needed, and then tells the agent how to use it.

If you also want the shared skill immediately:

```bash
