## Runtime Overrides

Use `{{ .Manifest.Env.HeadersJSON }}` for plain extra headers such as version pinning or undeclared non-auth headers.
Use `{{ .Manifest.Env.OverridesJSON }}` when the spec is missing auth metadata or a live endpoint has conditional input rules the spec does not express.

Header example:

```bash
export {{ .Manifest.Env.HeadersJSON }}='{"Clerk-API-Version":"2025-11-10"}'
{{ .Manifest.Name }} call {{ .ExampleOperation }}
```

Auth override example:

```bash
export API_TOKEN=...
export {{ .Manifest.Env.OverridesJSON }}='{"auth":{"headers":[{"name":"Authorization","env":"API_TOKEN","prefix":"Bearer ","required":true,"secret":true}]}}'
{{ .Manifest.Name }} call {{ .ExampleOperation }}
```

Conditional requirement example:

```bash
export {{ .Manifest.Env.OverridesJSON }}='{"operations":{"{{ .ExampleOperation }}":{"requirements":[{"when":[{"location":"query","name":"state","oneOf":["stopped","destroyed"]}],"require":[{"location":"query","name":"instance_id"}],"message":"query.instance_id is required when query.state is stopped or destroyed"}]}}}'
{{ .Manifest.Name }} call {{ .ExampleOperation }} --params '{"query":{"state":"stopped","instance_id":"..."}}'
```

